{
  "texts": [
    "This inclination may stem from the intricate nature that cognitive processing exhibits in artistic creation (Révész et al., 2017).",
    "Nonetheless, SR has demonstrated its utility as an effective facilitator, enabling arts educators to acquire profound insights into the cognitive aspects of art instruction and learning.",
    "For instance, dos Santos (2018) documented music teachers' approaches to the instruction of rhythmic skills as stimuli, facilitating their reflection upon their cognitive processes and their utilization of their didactic content knowledge.",
    "Linguistics and teacher education are two fields that more frequently took advantage of SR as a teaching strategy beyond research methods (Meade and McMeniman, 1992; Geiger et al., 2016; Sanchez and Grimshaw, 2019).",
    "Four articles in linguistics and three in teacher education explore using SR to improve participants' metacognition."
  ]
}